WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.959 --> 00:00:07.759
Tenerife is the largest of the seven Canary
Islands,

00:00:07.759 --> 00:00:13.110
a Spanish archipelago in the Atlantic Ocean,
off North Africa.

00:00:13.110 --> 00:00:15.469
Each of these volcanic islands are blessed

00:00:15.469 --> 00:00:19.580
with spectacular beaches, otherworldly beauty,

00:00:19.580 --> 00:00:21.520
and perfect weather.

00:00:31.440 --> 00:00:36.700
Tenerife receives around 5 million visitors
each year,

00:00:36.710 --> 00:00:39.840
many of whom head to the island’s seaside
resorts

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:44.120
to enjoy the year-round sunshine and spectacular
beaches.

00:00:50.850 --> 00:00:53.960
Enjoy golden sands and almost any watersport

00:00:53.960 --> 00:00:57.260
you can imagine at Las Americas Beach,

00:00:57.260 --> 00:00:59.730
one of the island’s most popular beaches.

00:00:59.730 --> 00:01:04.379
Or, take a dip in the crystal waters at Del
Duque Beach -

00:01:04.379 --> 00:01:07.239
just 10 minutes’ drive to the north.

00:01:13.380 --> 00:01:18.820
Los Cristianos ,once a sleepy fishing village is now a beachside town

00:01:18.829 --> 00:01:23.669
where you can step straight off the boardwalk
onto the soft sand.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.120
For a seaside experience with a difference,

00:01:32.130 --> 00:01:36.869
head to the north or west to discover sultry
black sand beaches.

00:01:36.869 --> 00:01:41.869
Visit Jardìn Beach…… or drive to Los
Gigantes,

00:01:41.869 --> 00:01:46.320
which nestles against the bottom of magnificent
cliffs.

00:01:49.620 --> 00:01:54.719
For those who can tear themselves away from
the island’s glorious beaches,

00:01:54.719 --> 00:01:58.149
Tenerife offers generous rewards.

00:01:58.149 --> 00:02:00.859
Some of the island’s most picturesque villages

00:02:00.859 --> 00:02:04.299
are only minutes away from the large resorts.

00:02:09.880 --> 00:02:13.880
Visit one of the two Canarian capitals,

00:02:13.890 --> 00:02:19.970
Santa Cruz de Tenerife. It is quirky, relaxed
and very Spanish…

00:02:19.970 --> 00:02:24.080
Pull up a chair at one of the restaurantes

00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:28.380
or stroll to the Auditorio de Tenerife Adán
Martín.

00:02:28.380 --> 00:02:32.620
The sail-like silhouette of this arts complex
has become a symbol

00:02:32.630 --> 00:02:41.390
of the archipelago and is a reminder of the
island’s long maritime history.

00:02:41.390 --> 00:02:44.780
Right beside the capital is San Cristóbal
de La Laguna,

00:02:44.780 --> 00:02:48.200
a city whose centre is so rich in history

00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:51.940
it has been declared a World Heritage Site.

00:02:56.680 --> 00:03:00.560
At the Southern end of the island is Costa
Adeje.

00:03:00.560 --> 00:03:05.200
Relax in the tropical parklandsof the Siam
Water Park,

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:08.720
or make a splash on one of the water rides.

00:03:10.650 --> 00:03:15.590
On the northwest coast lies Garachico,

00:03:15.590 --> 00:03:20.520
which was devastated by a volcanic eruption
in the 1700s.

00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:26.660
Today this pretty little town has rebuilt
itself and is a beautiful place to visit.

00:03:32.200 --> 00:03:37.440
Step even further back in time at Icod de
los Vinos,

00:03:37.440 --> 00:03:39.810
home to the ancient “Drago Milenario.”

00:03:39.810 --> 00:03:47.030
an Ancient Dragon Tree reputed to be more
than 1,000 years old.

00:03:47.720 --> 00:03:54.460
When massive seismic forces thrust this island
out of the ocean millions of years ago,

00:03:54.470 --> 00:03:58.190
it created some of the most spectacular landscapes

00:03:58.190 --> 00:03:59.300
in the world.

00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:14.280
Visit Teide National Park, the most visited
national park in Spain,

00:04:14.290 --> 00:04:16.770
and stand in awe of El Teide.

00:04:21.320 --> 00:04:23.260
This magnificent mountain is the highest in
all of Spain

00:04:23.270 --> 00:04:29.120
and was once believed by the lands’s indigenous
people to be the gateway to hell.

00:04:29.820 --> 00:04:31.319
If you like to hike,

00:04:31.319 --> 00:04:33.939
head to the small mountain village of Masca

00:04:33.939 --> 00:04:39.539
and spend the day following the Masca Gorge
all the way to the Atlantic Ocean.

00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:46.800
Ever since the golden age of discovery,

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:51.469
explorers and thinkers have been drawn to
Tenerife’s beautiful shores.

00:04:51.469 --> 00:04:57.830
In olden times, the trip was a perilous adventure
but today,

00:04:57.830 --> 00:05:01.030
Tenerife is an easy plane ride away.

00:05:03.599 --> 00:05:07.169
So, whether you are seeking ancient mysteries

00:05:07.169 --> 00:05:10.639
or escaping the modern stresses of daily life,

00:05:10.639 --> 00:05:14.840
come and discover all that Tenerife has to offer.

